The paper discusses the use of topic modeling and co-word mapping in research practices using moderately sized document collections, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, given the focus on text analysis and semantic mapping, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Other relevant sub-categories include Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
